						               													<description>New exclusive limited Edition 5555 copies! Completely bilingual German and French.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We are in 50 BC. All of Gaul is occupied by the Romans. All of Gaul? No! A village populated by indomitable Gauls never ceases to resist intruders. Take the role of a great leader and lead your people to victory not only through Gaul, but across the entire Roman Empire. Each nation has its own skills which greatly influence the game and from which tactical strategies can be developed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Complete secret missions to get victory points and decide the game for you. But beware! The magic potion will also surprise you in the game and bring you benefits or maybe steal your points. With sesterces you can buy new missions and units that strengthen you in the game and bring you closer to your goal of becoming the ruler of the Roman Empire.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;So, will you be able to use your skills victoriously or will another leader emerge as a glorious winner?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Get ready and brace yourself for the fight of a lifetime. With 2-5 players, ages 13 and up, you can muster your troops and join the defence of the conquests of Gaul or Caesar. You can choose from 2 different game modes. Distribute area cards evenly among all players and place your warriors on the field according to your cards. On your turn, you can attack neighbouring areas and, thanks to the various ports, even occupy coastal areas by sea. Roll the black dice to attack your opponents and use the red dice to defend yourself. If you manage to lead your attack profitably with the highest number of eyes, you can decide whether you want to keep fighting until you've taken out all enemy warriors or if you want to retreat first. This way, try to control as many areas as possible. 6 regions of different colours with a total of 45 areas must be conquered. Gaul with the largest land ownership wins the game. Potion Cards and Reinforcements provide special fun.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;So arm your troops and go with RISK Asterix in the battle for the Roman Empire and become a respected leader.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
